/*! \mainpage Img2Num Core Library
 *
 * \section intro_sec Introduction
 *
 * This is the heart of Img2Num. All implementations start here and are built upwards using this framework of functions
 * and libraries. C++ developers include this library directly, C developers include a lightweight wrapper around it,
 * and JavaScript
 * developers import a safe wrapper that protects them from manual memory management.
 *
 * The main raster image vectorization functions are located in this part of the libraryâ€”FFTs, contour tracing,
 * blurring,
 * and much more.
 *
 * \section features_sec Key Features
 *
 * All public functions are exported from `img2num.h`:
 * - Image processing algorithms (FFT, Contour Tracing, etc.)
 * - Memory management utilities
 * - Cross-platform compatibility
 *
 * \section building_sec Building Img2Num
 *
 * To build the project, follow these instructions:
 *
 * \code{.sh}
 * cmake -B build
 * cmake --build build
 * \endcode
 *
 * \section install_sec Installation
 *
 * To install the library, use the following commands:
 * \code{.sh}
 * cmake --install build
 * \endcode
 *
 * The library and headers will be installed as follows:
 * - **Libraries** are installed to `/usr/local/lib`
 * - **Headers** are installed to `/usr/local/include`
 *
 * To link to the library in your CMake project, use:
 * \code{.cmake}
 * find_package(Img2Num REQUIRED)
 * target_link_libraries(your_app PRIVATE Img2Num)
 * \endcode
 *
 * \section usage_sec Usage Example
 *
 * Here's a simple usage example in C++:
 * \code{.cpp}
 * #include <img2num.h>
 *
 * int main() {
 *     // Example usage of Img2Num functions
 *     Img2Num::processImage("input.png");
 *     return 0;
 * }
 * \endcode
 *
 * For complete working examples, see the `examples/` directory.
 *
 * \section api_sec API Reference
 *
 * Browse the detailed function documentation:
 * - \ref image_processing_group "Image Processing Algorithms"
 * - \ref memory_management_group "Memory Management Functions"
 */
